81
00:05:19,993 --> 00:05:26,943
Now let's see what mistakes happened to
me in Revolut and in my own projects.

82
00:05:27,443 --> 00:05:29,003
So the first mistake.

83
00:05:29,073 --> 00:05:32,073
My first mistake was giving
the model too much freedom.

84
00:05:32,513 --> 00:05:37,043
In the beginning, my prompt was basically
build a feature, a few screenshots,

85
00:05:37,043 --> 00:05:38,913
a short description, and let's go.

86
00:05:39,423 --> 00:05:40,493
And the feature was built.

87
00:05:40,903 --> 00:05:43,073
That is the very dangerous part.

88
00:05:43,563 --> 00:05:45,033
The output often works.

89
00:05:45,063 --> 00:05:48,963
It compiles, the screen opens,
the heavy pass is fine, and you

90
00:05:48,973 --> 00:05:50,633
feel like magic just happened.

91
00:05:51,353 --> 00:05:54,193
But after a few weeks,
the cost starts to appear.

92
00:05:54,763 --> 00:05:59,453
The model chooses its own abstraction,
creates new managers, introduces

93
00:05:59,453 --> 00:06:03,513
