And indie projects had also the
scope of different specific issues.

135
00:08:37,453 --> 00:08:39,893
The first thing is anarchy.

136
00:08:40,313 --> 00:08:44,683
AI build an anarchy inside my
project, especially at the beginning.

137
00:08:45,503 --> 00:08:50,653
There is no existing architecture
forcing the model to behave.

138
00:08:51,273 --> 00:08:55,843
So you are the architect, and if you
don't have the whole picture AI will

139
00:08:55,843 --> 00:08:58,263
happily invent one for every task.

140
00:08:58,373 --> 00:09:02,643
In my first project, I gave AI
agents a lot of freedom and mostly

141
00:09:02,653 --> 00:09:04,263
validated the product results.

142
00:09:04,703 --> 00:09:05,703
Does the screen work?

143
00:09:05,803 --> 00:09:07,223
Does the flow match the design?

144
00:09:07,223 --> 00:09:08,923
Does the feature behave correctly?

145
00:09:09,443 --> 00:09:10,943
And the product moved fast.

146
00:09:10,953 --> 00:09:12,743
As I said before, it moved super fast.

147
00:09:13,243 --> 00:09:17,563
But the code started collecting duplicates
